{"id":1732,"date":"2011-12-05T09:32:01","date_gmt":"2011-12-05T14:32:01","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=1732"},"modified":"2023-05-02T11:46:35","modified_gmt":"2023-05-02T07:46:35","slug":"dua-depression-anxiety","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/12\/05\/dua-depression-anxiety\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Distress: Dua to say when anxious or depressed"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Mas&#8217;ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>A servant is not struck by worry or grief but let him say, \u2018O Allah, I am Your servant, the son of Your servant, the son of Your maidservant. My forelock is in Your hand, Your decision over me has passed, and Your decree upon me is in justice. I ask You by every name with which You have named Yourself, or revealed in Your Book, or taught to one of Your creatures, or kept hidden in the Unseen with You, that You make the Quran the spring of my heart, the light within me, the banisher of my depression, and the expeller of my anxiety,\u2019 then Allah will expel his worry and replace his grief with joy.<\/strong>\u201d It was said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, shall we not study these words?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Of course, whoever hears them should study them<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 3712<\/p>\n<p>Grade:\u00a0<strong><em>Sahih\u00a0<\/em><\/strong>(authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0639\u064f\u0648\u062f\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u064